The paper deals with the computational complexity of a problem related to graph theory, specifically the existence of disconnected cuts and 2K2 partitions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves proving NP-completeness, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper deals with graph theory, which is covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
